<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-25T02:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-25T02:35:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/372: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-25T11:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">June 25,
                                        1927—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 25—7:16
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[43.] Draft of new contract has been submitted formally by Minister of
                            Finance to Millspaugh for his approval. Millspaugh <pb facs="0654" n="552" xml:id="pg_552"/> regards new terms as entirely
                            inadmissible, and he is drawing up for the Prime Minister a long
                            exposition of his own views.</p>
                        <p>The Minister of Finance, as perhaps also the Government, appears to wish
                            to deprive Doctor Millspaugh and the other Americans of their essential
                            powers and to break up their close unity of organization, or to obtain
                            the resignation of Doctor Millspaugh himself.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>